(102, 1, '2018-09-13 13:21:35', '2018-09-13 13:21:35', '<strong>Works as advertised. Nothing less, nothing more. Begginers: Yes; Professionals: No</strong>\r\n\r\nI purchased this keyboard as an absolute beginner to learn to play on as an adult. Knowing I would have limited time to practice I was looking for an affordable option that would not break the bank. After reading other reviews this seemed to be a viable option so I pulled the trigger. So keep in mind that my review comes from the position of an absolute beginner and here are my thoughts...\r\n\r\nThis keyboard is a good option for a beginner to learn on before moving on to a more expensive option if you decide you do enjoy the hobby. The keyboard works exactly as advertised. Nothing more, nothing less. I do feel like anyone with experience playing on a nicer or professional keyboard would not enjoy playing on this one as the keys have a \"toy like\" feel and spring to them. But overall everything works as it should. I\'m not overly blown away, but it gets the job done. I feel certain this will be all the keyboard I need to learn how to properly play music. With that said I will finish off with some pro\'s and con\'s.\r\n\r\n<strong>Pro\'s:</strong>\r\n-Comes with a fairly sturdy stand, nice seat, decent head phones and mic (have not used the mic)\r\n-Lots of different options as far as instruments and backup beats to choose from\r\n-Decent sounding speakers if you choose not to use the headphones\r\n-Keys are easy to play and move freely\r\n-Good beginner setup to learn on\r\n-works as advertised\r\n-items were well packaged\r\n\r\n<strong>Con\'s:</strong>\r\n-My biggest Con - DOES NOT COME WITH A 10v POWER ADAPTER. There IS a place to plug in a power adapter on the back of the keyboard yet it did NOT come with one in the box. I had to find one from another appliance I had around the house. Yes, you can use this keyboard with batteries but it did not come with those either. I feel like most people would rather plug it in then use batteries. My opinion would have been to leave the mic out and include a power adapter. I think more people would use the adapter then the mic.\r\n-keys seem very toy like. They have a spring like feel to them and are a little noisy\r\n-the music sheet holder sits in the rail very loosely so if you bump it at all it will fall off. Anything heavy falls off.\r\n-when the instrument is set to standard piano, low keys sound fine but the high keys sound a little off, a little digital (no pun intended)\r\n-the on/off button is like something off of an early 1980s toy. It is not a huge deal but it does seem like the one thing that is out of place\r\n\r\nIf they would have included a power adapter and the keys had just slightly better feel, I would have given 5 stars. In the end though I would recommend this for a beginner.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Hamzer-Portable-Electronic-Headphones-Microphone/dp/B0714JFQ7F/ref=sr_1_4?s=musical-instruments&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1536844482&amp;sr=1-4&amp;keywords=pianos#customerReviews\"><strong>Buy Here</strong></a>', 'Hamzer 61-Key Portable Electronic Keyboard Piano with Stand, Stool, Headphones & Microphone', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '99-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-09-13 13:21:35', '2018-09-13 13:21:35', '', 99, 'http://musicreview/uncategorized/99-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(103, 1, '2018-09-13 13:26:31', '2018-09-13 13:26:31', '<h4><strong>Great piano set &amp; great price</strong>\r\n<strong>STAND:</strong></h4>\r\nI feel the piano set stand works quit well. Once you have everything tightened and the key board actually attached to it, it all feels very sturdy. I love that it is adjustable in height. I purchased this for my 5 yr old, (although it can be used for an adult as well), and the adjustable stand brought the keyboard down to just the right height for her. (it goes pretty low to normal height)\r\n<h4><strong>SEAT:</strong></h4>\r\nThe piano set seat is not adjustable, but since the stand is, so it doesn\'t matter. The seat is a bit small. It\'s probably fine for a very small adult and children. But if you are an average to larger size person like me, then you will want to purchase the piano separately and get a larger keyboard/piano setbench.\r\n<h4><strong>HEADPHONES:</strong></h4>\r\nnot a very good quality. They crackle at times. I use a child\'s headphone set because it limits the volume output.\r\n<h4><strong>LCD SCREEN:</strong></h4>\r\nIs nice. If you want to know what a key is, you just press the key and it shows up on the grand staff on the screen. But I use sticker notes for my daughter, and you can see them better. Nice to have a built in metronome.\r\n<h4><strong>CON:</strong></h4>\r\n(-1 star) Every time you turn the keyboard on, the default volume is max, and you have to adjust it. I don\'t see a place where I can change this to default to a lower setting. My casio turns down extremely low, and when I turn it off, the next time I use it, it is still at the volume I left it on. I wish that is how this one was.\r\n<h4><strong>KEYS:</strong></h4>\r\nI find these keys are stiffer than my Casio keys. I was worried about my 5yr old being able to use them, but she seems to do fine with them, so they must not be that stiff.\r\n<h4><strong>OVERALL:</strong></h4>\r\ngreat set &amp; great price for a beginner.\r\n\r\n<a hre